item.dc:creator: snearch
item.description: With consumer now officially being declared dead, B2B/enterprise is what’s in. It makes sense for a lot of reasons. The most compelling reason for founders is that it’s less of a gamble because you know that the success of your company ultimately depends on making a sale. It’s bimodal: you’re either solving a problem worth solving (people will pay) or you’re not (people won’t pay). As opposed to betting on creating something that people may or may not find useful, depending on their mood.
